Exercice : 
- Create the element <h1>CHATE</h1> using JavaScript 
- The CSS properties are as follows and must be added using JavaScript :
    color: blue;
    font-size: 80px;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: Arial

 

HTML :

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <script src="03-main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>


JS : 

document.write("<h1>CHATE</h1>");
document.querySelector("h1").style.color = "Blue";
document.querySelector("h1").style.fontSize = "80px";
document.querySelector("h1").style.fontWeight = "bold";
document.querySelector("h1").style.textAlign = "center";
document.querySelector("h1").style.fontFamily = "Arial";
